# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Annix Read needs ONE AI provider configured. Pick the cheapest / easiest:
#
#   Option 1 — Gemini Flash (FREE, recommended)
#     1. Go to https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
#     2. Click "Create API key" — no credit card needed
#     3. Paste below as GOOGLE_API_KEY
#     Free tier: 1500 requests/day, plenty for a free educational tool.
#
#   Option 2 — Ollama (FREE, offline, no key, no signup)
#     1. Install Ollama from https://ollama.ai/download
#     2. Run: ollama pull llama3.1
#     3. Set ENABLE_OLLAMA=1 below
#     100% offline, never calls any external service.
#
#   Option 3 — Claude (best quality, ~$0.10 per book)
#     Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com/
#     Set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY below.
#
#   Option 4 — Zero APIs: pre-cache the seeded books once on a friend's
#     machine that has any of the above, then ship the resulting
#     data/annix_read.db. The 60 seeded books work forever, no key needed.
#     See `python -m app.precache --help`.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Uncomment one of these:

# GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-gemini-key-here
# ENABLE_OLLAMA=1
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# Optional advanced settings:
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.1

# Optional: host/port for uvicorn
HOST=127.0.0.1
PORT=8000
